      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_medicine_preclinical_l3_muscle_contraction",
      "content": {
        "title": "Motor Unit Recruitment and Force Grading",
        "definition": "Progressive activation of motor units by size (Henneman size principle) to grade muscle force from small slow units to large fast units.",
        "summary": "Recruitment and rate coding modulate tension. Type I fibers for endurance; type II for power."
      },
